msContents.summary: Arabic-Syriac glossary divided by topic. Each entry consists of an Arabic word, its Syriac equivalent and the transliteration of the Syriac into Arabic letters.

author.name: J. Rendel Harris Collection (Quaker & Special Collections, Haverford College)

supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil added, upper left recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh and Syriac in black ink; pointed, partially vocalized.

binding.p: Modern European binding; maroon half covers with SYR.ARAB stamped on the spine; red speckled edges.

origin.p: Item is undated, an owner's notes places it in the first half of the 20th century, but it was likely compiled in the late 19th century.
